title: Netanyahu says ‘no way’ to eliminate Hamas without Rafah operation
description: The Israeli prime minister remained defiant, even as U.S. officials summoned an Israeli delegation to Washington to discuss an attack on Rafah.

title: Deadlock on U.S. aid hangs over talks to secure support for Ukraine
description: A meeting of Ukraine’s backers underscored the uncomfortable dynamic the U.S. must navigate as it seeks to lead the effort while unable to guarantee its own support.

title: More than 20 killed in Somalia in alleged Turkish drone strike
description: The strike just outside the Somali capital killed more than 22 people and wounded 21, including many children, a witness and a relative of the victims said.

title: Supreme Court clears way for Texas to enforce immigration law, for now
description: The decision on Texas’s State Bill 4 was preliminary. Justices urged a lower court to decide whether to allow the law to stay in effect while appeals continue.

title: Generals who carried out Biden’s Afghan exit face new GOP scrutiny
description: Retired generals Mark Milley and Kenneth McKenzie discuss President Biden’s withdrawal from Afghanistan before the GOP-led House Foreign Affairs Committee.

title: Police: Anti-vax Bolsonaro forged vaccine card before U.S. visit
description: The former Brazilian president had spent years inveighing against the coronavirus vaccine and had sworn off ever receiving one.

title: How many hostages are still in Gaza since Hamas attack on Israel? What to know.
description: Israel estimates some 112 hostages held by Hamas have been released or freed; 97 are believed still to be alive in Gaza. Here’s what we know.

title: Drone footage raises questions about Israeli justification for deadly strike on Gaza journalists
description: Footage recovered from the drone of an Al Jazeera team killed by the IDF in a targeted Jan. 7 missile strike raises critical questions about the Israeli justification for the attack.

title: In Gambia, parliament moves toward overturning ban on female genital cutting
description: If the ban on female genital cutting is overturned, this tiny West African nation would be the first to roll back such a protection as debate rages over religion, culture, patriarchy and women’s health.

title: Hong Kong fast-tracks law that once drew protests, cementing Beijing’s hold
description: Hong Kong’s legislature, stacked with pro-Beijing lawmakers, passed laws that bring it under tighter Chinese control. Law and journalist groups decried the vote.

title: Blinken boosts U.S. ties to Philippines amid China maritime aggression
description: Philippine President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. is seeking to fortify his nation against Beijing, taking a much more assertive stance toward China than his predecessor, Rodrigo Duterte.

title: Paris Olympics security fears are clashing with ‘Games wide open’ pledge
description: Organizers have scaled back a grand plan to make the Opening Ceremonies on the Seine river widely accessible and free to most.

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Israel to send team to D.C. to discuss Rafah; Blinken will return to Mideast
description: Biden is concerned that an Israeli offensive in Rafah would worsen the humanitarian toll and hurt Israel’s long-term security, his national security adviser said.

title: Israel’s war on Hamas brings famine to Gaza
description: What makes this calamity all the more stunning is that it’s entirely the product of human decisions.
